{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"1. **Overrides directory hashing** — `hashBuildContext()` replaces the simple `hashBytes(dockerfileContent)`. It hashes the Dockerfile content plus all files in `.cloche/overrides/` using a deterministic sorted walk. File paths are included in the hash so renames are detected.","timestamp":"2026-03-05T02:53:36.224526668Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-05T02:53:36.224553008Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"2. **Base image digest tracking** — `parseFromImage()` extracts the FROM image from the Dockerfile. `checkBaseImageStaleness()` pulls the base image and compares its digest to the one stored as a `cloche.baseimage.digest` label on the built image. If different, triggers a rebuild.","timestamp":"2026-03-05T02:53:36.224558117Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-05T02:53:36.224569188Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"3. **Rate-limited pulls** — `shouldPullBase()` checks a timestamp file (`.cloche/.last-base-pull`) to avoid pulling more than once per hour.","timestamp":"2026-03-05T02:53:36.224574097Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-05T02:53:36.224584748Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"4. **Updated `buildImage()`** — Now accepts a `baseDigest` parameter and stores it as a label alongside the context hash. No changes to the `ImageEnsurer` interface were needed.","timestamp":"2026-03-05T02:53:36.224590949Z"}
